    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Beginning at 15th level, you can extend the benefit of your Indomitable feature to an ally. When you decide to use Indomitable to reroll a saving throw and you are not incapacitated, you can choose one ally within 60 feet of you that also failed its saving throw against the same effect. If that creature can see or hear you, it can reroll its saving throw, adding their proficiency bonus to the save if they are not already proficient in it, and must use the new roll.</p>",
